response.Q0: I thought it was better to inspect the farthest nodes because that was where you could earn the most cash or lose the most cash. The nodes closer to the spider felt inconsequential as they usually did not reward a large amount of cash or resulted in a large loss.
response.Q1: I used to look at more nodes closer to the spider in the beginning or tried random nodes. Later on I tried to find numbers that were in the 80s or 70s and stopped my search then and there.
response.Q2: It was difficult as you have to balance how much money you are losing to inspect nodes and hoping to find one that will pay off. If you can't find one that will pay a large amount sometimes you will have to cut your losses and go for a node path that gives less cash.

response.Q1: I felt like the spider was familiar but the game felt completely different to what I played before. The web felt bigger here and I don't remember a node inspector.
